{"body": "Section 142) **\u201cChild\u201d and  \u201cqualifying young person\u201d**\n\n1) For the purposes of this Part of this Act a person is a child if he has not attained the age of 16. \n2) In this Part of this Act  \u201cqualifying young person\u201d means a person, other than a child, who \u2014 \n\ta) has not attained such age (greater than 16) as is prescribed by regulations made by the Treasury, and \n\tb) satisfies conditions so prescribed. ", "citation_label": "1992 c. 4 s. 142", "citation_path": "uk/statute/ukpga/1992/4/142", "document_class": "statute", "expression_date": "2026-06-01-uk-frs-microsim", "heading": "\u201cChild\u201d and \u201cqualifying young person\u201d", "id": "63f189b5-9096-585c-9c90-2e9b18dd9226", "identifiers": {"legislation.gov.uk:number": "4", "legislation.gov.uk:provision": "142", "legislation.gov.uk:type": "ukpga", "legislation.gov.uk:year": "1992"}, "jurisdiction": "uk", "kind": "section", "language": "en", "legal_identifier": "1992 c. 4 s. 142", "level": 1, "metadata": {"extent": [], "references_to": [], "retrieved_at": "2026-06-01"}, "ordinal": 142, "parent_citation_path": "uk/statute/ukpga/1992/4", "parent_id": "797db604-822f-50b7-8914-43679d8ced49", "source_as_of": "2026-06-01-uk-frs-microsim", "source_document_id": "ukpga/1992/4", "source_format": "lex.lab.i.ai.gov.uk", "source_id": "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/1992/4/section/142", "source_path": "sources/uk/statute/2026-06-01-uk-frs-microsim/ukpga/1992/4/section-142.json", "source_url": "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/1992/4/section/142", "version": "2026-06-01-uk-frs-microsim"}
